43:48.249 --> 43:51.450
ready to pop
out of their button fly.

43:51.452 --> 43:52.654
Pop!

43:53.653 --> 43:54.954
Pop!"

43:54.956 --> 43:57.323
We got it. Pop!

43:57.325 --> 44:00.358
- Pop! It's all about penises, please.
- Oh, stop.

44:00.360 --> 44:03.329
And just like that,
some cowboy stops me

44:03.331 --> 44:05.330
and says my poem is X-rated.

44:05.332 --> 44:07.899
And you don't think it was?

44:07.901 --> 44:09.468
No. It wasn't.

44:09.470 --> 44:11.570
It was a red-blooded,
American poem.

44:11.572 --> 44:13.472
All right.

44:13.474 --> 44:15.608
So, the cowboy tells me
to stop, and I say to him,

44:15.610 --> 44:18.611
"I'm an American
reading an American poem

44:18.613 --> 44:21.347
about an American institution."

44:21.349 --> 44:22.948
He didn't like that.

44:22.950 --> 44:25.283
He accused me of being drunk.

44:25.285 --> 44:28.553
I say to him, "I've been sober
now for three years.

44:28.555 --> 44:31.423
I'm a proud member of A.A."

44:31.425 --> 44:32.957
And I walked off.

44:32.959 --> 44:36.028
Anyone want to respond
to Martingale's story?

44:36.030 --> 44:38.930
Well, the poems make
straight guys angry.

44:38.932 --> 44:41.399
- I'm not angry, Hans.
- See?

44:41.401 --> 44:43.901
But here's the thing:
that kind of anger

44:43.903 --> 44:46.472
can get in the way
of your recovery.

44:46.474 --> 44:49.475
I think we can all agree
that being out there

44:49.477 --> 44:52.977
and having a good time...
not drinking, we get it...

44:52.979 --> 44:54.445
feels really good.

44:54.447 --> 44:56.582
But it's one thing
to read your poems

44:56.584 --> 44:58.383
in front of people
that you know

44:58.385 --> 45:00.419
in your Greek cafes
late at night,

45:00.421 --> 45:03.354
but it's another to read it in
front of rednecks at a rodeo.

45:03.356 --> 45:05.356
It's a little bit dangerous.

45:05.358 --> 45:07.026
- I think he was really brave.
- Mm.

45:07.028 --> 45:08.526
- Yeah, I do, too, Martingale.
- Yeah.

45:08.528 --> 45:10.361
- I mean, I...
- Fuck the rednecks, right?

45:10.363 --> 45:11.729
- That's right.
- Hey. I'm a mullet-haired redneck,

45:11.731 --> 45:13.332
and you know
I'll kick your ass.

45:13.334 --> 45:14.666
You know I can kick your ass.

45:14.668 --> 45:16.334
- John, any comments?
- What?

45:16.336 --> 45:17.572
John.

45:18.706 --> 45:20.571
What I want to know is,

45:20.573 --> 45:22.408
with all the poems
that you have,

45:22.410 --> 45:24.343
they can't all be
about penises.

45:24.345 --> 45:26.445
I mean, you probably got
some pretty ones, I'm sure.

45:26.447 --> 45:27.713
Well, what I believe

45:27.715 --> 45:31.450
is we all have led,
in our non-sober periods,

45:31.452 --> 45:33.352
somewhat chaotic lives.

45:33.354 --> 45:37.423
And I think there's
a very fine line between

45:37.425 --> 45:40.358
creating chaos
because of the adventure

45:40.360 --> 45:44.265
and creating chaos because
of the dependency on it.

45:45.532 --> 45:47.099
Now, John isn't
speaking very much,

45:47.101 --> 45:49.702
so perhaps he thinks
he's better than us.

45:49.704 --> 45:52.307
So, John, do you want
to tell us about your drinking?

45:54.108 --> 45:56.642
Oh.

45:56.644 --> 45:59.410
Is this... Do I say,
"John, I'm an alcoholic"?

45:59.412 --> 46:01.483
Just tell us
about your drinking.

46:04.385 --> 46:06.517
Um...

46:06.519 --> 46:08.454
Well, I, um,

46:08.456 --> 46:12.059
I started drinking
when I was, uh, 13.

46:14.095 --> 46:16.128
Um...

46:16.130 --> 46:20.535
I-I stole a bottle of gin
from my Aunt Diane.

46:21.635 --> 46:25.003
And, um, I liked it.

46:25.005 --> 46:27.439
A lot.

46:27.441 --> 46:29.010
And I never stopped.

46:30.443 --> 46:31.709
Okay.

46:31.711 --> 46:34.812
Um, yeah...

46:34.814 --> 46:36.615
Keep going.

46:36.617 --> 46:41.553
I mean, I-I kept drinking,
I guess,

46:41.555 --> 46:44.390
maybe because I was adopted.

46:44.392 --> 46:46.392
I was adopted.

46:46.394 --> 46:49.026
And, um,

46:49.028 --> 46:52.530
maybe it made me
not care as much about that.

46:52.532 --> 46:55.401
Or...

46:55.403 --> 46:57.135
Yeah.

46:57.137 --> 46:59.405
I-I don't, I don't really know.

46:59.407 --> 47:02.508
- Yeah...
- Corky drank 'cause her name is Corky.

47:05.613 --> 47:07.845
I drank 'cause my shoes
were too tight.

47:07.847 --> 47:09.847
You know,

47:09.849 --> 47:12.417
I'm glad you find this amusing.

47:12.419 --> 47:13.718
John, what we're trying
to point out

47:13.720 --> 47:15.454
is that we all have excuses.

47:15.456 --> 47:17.856
I resent you characterizing

47:17.858 --> 47:20.492
such a painful part
of my childhood,

47:20.494 --> 47:23.398
such as being an orphan,
as an excuse.

47:24.697 --> 47:28.834
I mean,
it is a fact, among others.

47:28.836 --> 47:30.836
Like, for instance,
I can't move

47:30.838 --> 47:32.671
one fucking muscle
below my chest.

47:32.673 --> 47:34.807
Would that qualify as an excuse?

47:34.809 --> 47:38.142
- What are you laughing at?
- We were waiting for that.

47:38.144 --> 47:40.445
We just knew you were gonna
say that, that's all.

47:40.447 --> 47:42.146
- You fucking cow!
- Oh.

47:42.148 --> 47:43.682
You wouldn't know pain
if it crawled up

47:43.684 --> 47:45.149
your fucking ass
and devoured you!

47:45.151 --> 47:46.218
How dare you!

47:46.220 --> 47:48.187
I'm sorry.
Well...

47:50.157 --> 47:53.827
...as a matter of fact,
I have cancer of the heart.

47:57.164 --> 47:58.863
And just let me
tell you something

47:58.865 --> 48:01.166
about your "poor me" s, okay?

48:01.168 --> 48:03.535
You keep it up,
"poor me, poor me,"

48:03.537 --> 48:05.102
and you're gonna
find yourself saying,

48:05.104 --> 48:06.738
- "Pour me another drink."
- Mm.

48:06.740 --> 48:09.140
And for the record,

48:09.142 --> 48:12.644
when I first came here,
I was a fat, worthless cow.

48:12.646 --> 48:14.646
But I worked these 12 steps,

48:14.648 --> 48:17.548
and I carved out a little bit
of a life for myself.

48:17.550 --> 48:19.486
I'm sorry, Reba.

48:20.753 --> 48:22.153
I'm sorry, everybody.

48:22.155 --> 48:23.921
- It's okay.
- It's expected.

48:23.923 --> 48:27.225
It's okay, John.

48:27.227 --> 48:30.762
You're right on schedule,
sweetheart.

48:30.764 --> 48:32.564
And I'm glad you're here.
I want to tell you that.

48:32.566 --> 48:34.836
- Thank you.
- I'm glad you're here.

48:41.242 --> 48:43.274
I like you guys.

48:43.276 --> 48:46.245
You're fucking crazy.

48:49.517 --> 48:51.517
